'Moonlight' (2016) - This film is utterly flawless. A24 in my opinion is a breeding-ground for near-perfect films, and this is one of the few that have actually turned out perfect. Everything from the screenplay, casting, acting, cinematography, editing, I was simply taken by all of it. There are few films that can hypnotize me and and keep me in its grasp from beginning to end, and this is one of those films. It is so subtle, and yet so powerful. It's not a movie that lets its actors goes over-the-top with emotion, but rather the opposite, keeping it bottled up and that makes it all-the-more realistic. As I mentioned, each performance given in this movie is impeccable. So many moments gave me chills and moved me to my core. I've never been so invested in a character-study movie before, and I find myself rewatching it over and over again, each time it getting better and better, picking up more slight details along the way. Easily one of the best movies of the 2010's, and of the best character-piece movies of the 21st century thus far, in my opinion.
