There were a lot of pros and cons to this movie for me. I think it's best I list them out.

PROS:
- absolutely beautifully shot (especially the monologues with disconnected sound and picture)
- structure was interesting and made it very easy to navigate
- second act was a huge highlight for me
- unique classical score that set a totally different tone from the cliche (where the cliche might have been hip-hop songs)

CONS:
- third act was a bore in my opinion
- I'm not a fan of giving such huge emphasis on race and identity in movies (people should be portrayed as who they are as naturally as possible, or else it gives rise to stereotypes and outdated movie tropes)
- the deliberate partitioning of the three acts made me want more out of the story. I love coming-of-age films, but leaving out the transitions between adolescence -> teen and teen -> adulthood was a little disappointing to me. And the sections can give us room for imagination, but the pacing made it hard for me to keep my interest in Chiron's development.
