I√¢(TM)ve seen this film one time before. I was 14. I remember thinking, √¢What did I just watch? What does this all mean?√¢? I was polarized. The fact that I completely understand this film two years later is beyond me. Moonlight is a deep MASTERPIECE that has to be seen to be believed. The film itself is a coming-of-age drama that unfolds in three acts: Little, Chiron, & Black. It√¢(TM)s about a young man, Chiron, who√¢(TM)s growing up in a hostile environment. The film follows his epic journey to adulthood which is lead by reinforcement, compassion, and love from surprising areas. Throughout the entire film, even into the final act of him as an adult, he√¢(TM)s a shy outsider continuously dealing with difficult circumstances. There are metaphors & morals all over this film. You, as the audience, have to use your THIRD EYE like never before because there is so much to unfold, to learn, to see. The movie feels so real. EVERYONE in their acting roles were so amazing and realistic. Especially near the end of the film. I actually thought I was watching a real conversation shown in front of me. The camerawork is magnetic, glossy & raw. It added to this realistic, somber flair that is this movie. The story structure itself is so pure and natural. It√¢(TM)s like you√¢(TM)re reading a book but more fluidly. There√¢(TM)s even music that speaks to the audience and becomes integral to the story√¢(TM)s metaphors & morals. The film√¢(TM)s main messages revolve around how society itself will look at you strangely just because of who you are. You can√¢(TM)t let ANYONE decide who YOU want to be and what YOU want to do. The film understands that precisely. The torment that you feel with our main character throughout is very resonant. What may seem pleasing to others when it comes to sexuality happens to be a nightmare for people like Chiron.. and MOST OF US DO NOT CARE TO UNDERSTAND THAT. √¢In moonlight, black boys look blue√¢?. This doesn√¢(TM)t mean that they√¢(TM)re sad, it means that they√¢(TM)re SPECIAL. It means that they√¢(TM)ve found something for THEMSELVES, not anyone else. They find themselves IN MOONLIGHT. Overall, Moonlight is a gut-wrenching, scary, emotional, stunningly mature film that speaks to the mind, body, & soul. 
