The beauty of Moonlight comes from the cultivation of drama that rises above mere event tragedy. The film operates on an intensely personal level, developing visually rather than audibly, and provides a deeply satisfying conclusion. Though the subject is so deeply niche, Moonlight is a story of relationships, and one in particular that touches the viewers heart.
