If Terrence Malick had directed a Spike Lee script it might well have become Moonlight. It's a wonderfully acted, borderline pretentious drama about a lonely child discovering his sexuality and honouring the human need for love. Barry Jenkins allows his cast to mumble inaudibly, which is occasionally frustrating, but it's an unusual and often very beautiful film with a great soundtrack.
