Moonlight is the last film to receive the academy award for best picture this year. Barry Jenkins has crafted a complicated coming of age story with a central hero who's incredibly complex and introverted. Beautifully shot, written and produced, the film follow the story of Chiron a young African American struggling with finding his place in this world and the constant bullying to which he is victim in school. We follow him through three main stages of his life, three portrait of a person trying to construct himself in a tough environment. This is an incredible film with a powerful message, a vibrant personal journey and a complex study of how African American men are trapped in the multiples ghetto-cliches we are used to see all the time of film and TV. Although the movie will not appeal to anyone, i really think it would be a miss to avoid watching it. It's such a rare thing nowadays to get the opportunity to watch such a beautifully crafted story with depth and brains. Please give it a go and make up your own mind.
