If you enjoy a good slice-of-life human drama, then I will say right from the outset you need to see Moonlight. It is broken up into 3 stages in a young man's life, as he struggles to connect with people and to discover his own identity. This is a very quiet film, largely because Chiron isn't a big talker. He's introverted, timid, and beaten down by life. The cast is amazing in every stage of the movie, and they change out almost all the actors every time the film transitions to the next time period. It's a heart-wrenching tale, one that many people will connect with because the themes are universal. So many of us have experienced being the outsider, and wondering what you are supposed to be. I can't complain about much with Moonlight because the film was well-shot, well-acted, and well-written. Honestly, the only thing I can say is that it's not the kind of film that I get super excited about watching. I was invested in it, and I think it is a solid story. However, it's the kind of heavy drama that I'm not drawn to, and the pacing is slow which doesn't suit me all that well. I will watch it again sometime, because I can't stop thinking about it, and I bet with a rewatch I will rate it even higher.
