MOONLIGHT-2016(R)-Feb. 3.
By:Clem The Movie Guy.

Each of us struggles in our individual journey growing up, & outside influences; environment, family and circumstances can have a profound effect. Moonlight is the powerful & captivating story of Chiron, a young black man & his journey of self-discovery from young adolescence to adulthood. Broken into three segments, the movie begins with Chiron as a skinny young kid (Alex R. Hibbert) living with his mother (Naomie Harris), a drug addict who prefers getting high to taking care of her son who's dealing with harassment over aspects of his sexuality that he is not even quite aware of yet. Chiron is befriended by the neighborhood drug dealer, Juan (Mahershala Ali) & his girlfriend, Teresa (Janelle Mon√°e) who provide a rare support & sanctuary. In segment two,  a teenage Chiron (Ashton Sanders) begins to explore his sexual identity with his one & only friend Kevin (Jharrel Jerome, teen verison). Believing that they had something special, Chiron is devastated by betrayal when Kevin is manipulated by school bully Terrel (Patrick Decile) to assault Chiron. In the third segment, Chiron, as an adult, attempts to understand & to recover the connections he has lost. Moonlight is based on the unproduced play "In Moonlight Black Boys Look Blue" by Tarell Alvin McCraney. Screenwriter Barry Jenkins has directed a marvelous & beautifully haunting story of life, love & self-discovery. The performances from the cast, which features Trevante Rhodes as Adult Chiron, Andr√© Holland as Adult Kevin, & Jaden Piner as Child Kevin were all phenomenal & emotional charged. Winner of the Best Picture at the Golden Globes, Moonlight has received eight Academy Award nominations including Best Picture, Barry Jenkins for Best Director & Best Adapted Screenplay, Best Supporting Actress (Naomie Harris), & Best Supporting Actor (Mahershala Ali). Moonlight is a MUST-SEE FILM & one that will end on my list of best films of 2016.
