Captivating and honest, in a 'Squid and the Whale' kind of way. Moonlight captures the lives of Chiron, and all of the various people in his life, incredibly believably. The performances were all great, especially (and surprisingly) the kids and teenagers. And there was just something about Chiron's silence in the first two acts that gave the film a unique kind of power. It was two hours long, and I felt like I could keep watching for however many more Barry Jenkins could push out. My main issue with the film is with the third act, in that I felt like the two actors primarily featured could've used one more take on each scene, just to absolutely nail it. Also, could've used more Mahershala Ali, he was fantastic.
