"This movie also skips over so much. The guy at the beginning dies and you never hear how he dies and it pissed me off. Then the guy gets arrested and you never hear how anything turns out. " ---  After I saw this comment in another review, I realized this was one of the primary reasons why I LIKED THIS MOVIE: I treated me like  grown up.  It did not spoon feed me every detail for detail sake. It allowed me to make my own story about what happened, and the surprising thing was that some of those assumptions were stereotypical and even borderline racist.  I was not expecting that.  But a little self awareness is a good thing, and this film intentionally or unintentionally did that for me.
