Good thing I got a screener and didn't pay for a babysitter and movie tickets.  I really hoped I'd love this movie.  What's the hype?  No one likes a black-kid-with-a-crack-addicted-mom movie more than me.  No one. And yet, this just bored me to sleep. Literally.  Took 3 nights to see it and lots of late afternoon coffee to try to stay awake.  I think I get it why it's getting all the great reviews.  I get it.  It's a black movie.  We need them.  The more the merrier.  We also need to address bullying.  Let's make some more bullying movies please.  We also need more gay movies.  Let's please make some gay movies but where the gay men actually seem gay, even if just for 3.  So after having watched "Broke Black Mountain," let me just say that I was utterly disappointed.  No action.  Zero plot.  "Boyhood" had more plot and that didn't have a plot either.  Minimal action. Barely any dialogue (I guess the introverts are in this awards season... i.e., Casey Affleck in "Manchester By the Sea").   Casting was just totally not good (3 actors depicting 3 stages of life didn't even resemble each other).  No really sweet and tender moments.  Plus, these guys are in Miami.  How repressed and closeted can you be in a city where at least 5% of its population falls into the LGBT category? I really wanted to see a kid that struggled in youth grow up to go away to college and get his shit together and get married to a gay man in San Francisco.  There was no character growth for any of the characters. Sorry, this just didn't work for me and based on the description of this movie, this should have been "my" movie this year.  A real snoozer, this movie was. Moving onto the next....
