Needless to say, the acting, cinematography, directing, and even scoring are all exceptional, but what truly stands out in Moonlight is it's ability to portray how a person can change based on the events that transpire in one's life. How certain things can make you curl up into a ball, never to be unraveled again - or as the movie calls it "going hard"- which is precisely what Chiron goes through in the three stages of his life. For that alone, I tip Barry Jenkins my hat, for the masterpiece he has created will touch many souls around the world who have gone through the same transformation.
