This poetic film that chronicles three stages in the life of a black kid (eventually teen and adult in each respective chapter) who struggles in his coming of age, dealing with his addict mother as well as his own sexual identity.  It's a well made, and subtle, film that grapples with it's subject matter with maturity and beauty and sorrow.
