Moonlight offers a special perspective on life. As I followed Chiron through the span of his life, I developed a close connection with the character. The acting of Little, Chiron, and Black was so powerful that I felt a lot of the struggles and emotional setbacks that the character felt. This movie showed me how dealing with sexuality is a part of life and sometimes it can be very confusing to people. I truly loved this film's direction, character development, plot, script, and musical score. There are not a lot of movies that leave me with the kind of indescribable feeling that Moonlight gave me, which is why I rate it 5/5 stars.
