A moving, unconventional film about a black man, Chiron, growing up in Miami. He comes under the influence of a drug dealer who he meets in an abandoned apartment, deals with his mother's addiction issues, gets taunted in school, lashes out, and ultimately connects with another young man, Kevin. The last of three sections brings him back together with Kevin after they've been separated by time and distance for a quiet, terse, nostalgic, and affecting reunion. The film is understated and involving with good acting and a glimpse of a community not frequently depicted on film and almost never in this way.
