A raw and heartfelt meditation on love, sexuality, masculinity and growing up. Where this film truly succeeds are in all the small ways other movies often miss: the way characters watch each other, change their posture when around each other, the basics of human interaction that we all know and experience every day, laid bare for the camera. This one deserves every ounce of praise it receives.
