This is probably one of the most interesting movies I have seen this year. It is three periods in the life of a gay black man, from childhood to adult. A dope fiend mother, constant bullying in school, a hint of love, and betrayal lead to a sort of resolution, albeit not a happy one, as an adult. This movie is almost perfect as a picture of a life. You might not catch it as it is an Indie in limited release, but if you have the chance go for sure. Not my usual pick with action but still a movie I am thinking about days later, worth the effort.
