Moonlight is one of the best films I've seen. It centers Black, queer identities without trapping the characters in a narrative of trauma. This is a piece of truth that centers Black queer identities, and it's done beautifully. The actors are all brilliant, the script is groundbreaking, and all in all, this is a groundbreaking film and a remarkable piece of cinema.
