This movie is so good, the first 15 minutes build-up had me so enticed despite its simplicity, this movie delves into something so unique, something that movies really don't ever venture into;
The cycle of a man's life, a drug dealer and a drug taker raising a young gay boy into a young gay teen into a drug dealer limited of his sexuality.

This film explains in such a brutal way that your upbringing creates you, if you get called a Faggot enough times, you will question it, you get called "Black" enough times, you just accept it. As Kevin says at the end of the film "Who are you [Chiron]?" in which he replies with "I'm just me", an innocent boy bullied with a mother he hates will produce a different man. I don't fully believe this film quite follows the narrow description of "a movie about two gay black boys" rather you become what you see. Kevin punching Chiron in the face isn't what he wanted, its what he is, his compassionate attitude towards Chiron cannot uphold in the life he made for himself, there is a serious struggle and limitation with trying to pursue a gay lifestyle in the black community, which is why Kevin as a man completely neglects it by having a kid.

