'MOONLIGHT' is a cinematic experience that transcend its' own social constraints to live with its' own pulsing heartbeat; Such intricacy of humanity has seldom been as magnificently portrayed. Director Barry Jenkins' narrative studies the life of a beautiful man, examining his hardships and finding strength in his reality. The film is poetic, wordlessly delicate yet fierce and uncompromising, and the performances by all are exquisite -- most notably that of Ashton Sanders and Trevante Rhodes. This is a film that speaks of purest artistry and celebrates the beauty of life that triumphs despite current political tyranny.
