Went to see this movie tonight.  I think the plot was very original in that it showed someone's life in three parts.  It was well acted by the whole cast.  Very believable.  There was some awkward moments in the film and some points in which the film didn't show that would have made it better.  I must admit the ending had me like what the.... was that it?  Over all it was a good coming of age movie.  Real impressed with Janelle's acting chops?
Moonlight was a lot different than I expected and when first leaving the theater I did not feel it was worth all of the acclaim that it has been getting. Now that some time has settled I think that the movie was very good. An Oscar contender maybe...the winner I dont believe so. 

Nonetheless the film tells the story in 3 phases of Chiron; as a child, teenager and adult. The movie explores what it is like growing up and being bullied in an African American neighborhood. It is about a boy who cannot be himself because everything around him is telling him to be somebody else. Chiron struggles with being reserved in a brutal neighborhood, he struggles with his sexuality, and he struggles with home life, and he struggles with finding himself. 

The movie is emotional in that you can feel what Chiron feels. The acting is top notch and the story is an important one to tell. The problem is with the odd cinematography that attempts to be unique but comes off at jerky and not fluid. The film also does not have a lot of direction. The first two acts are near perfect, with the third losing the steam. A good film worth watching, but short of perfect.
