It's rare when I don't really enjoy a movie that has gotten amazing reviews. I just didn't connect with this at all. I will say I enjoyed the acting very much. All were great. Naomie Harris was the stand out for me & wouldn't mind if she got the Oscar for this role. Mahershala Ali was good but his role was too small to leave a lasting impression on me. When it comes to Supporting Actors he isn't a stand out for me of the year. The music was also great. But that's about all I liked from the movie. Sad to say. Normally I don't want to say too many negative things about a movie when I don't like it, but since this one is gonna get a lot of Oscar love I just feel like I need to explain why I didn't like it. I'll try to keep it short. While this was amazing subject matter, had so much potential, I felt the storytelling & filming fell short. It was so slow. While it is a grim story I felt no emotional connection. Things would happen without explanation. Also the dialogue wasn't for me. The camerawork also made me a bit sick. The constant spinning, the blurry shots, made my eyes hurt. I will say there were at least 3 absolutely stunning shots though. But the camerawork pulled me out of the movie too much. I am glad this movie was made & hope it opens the door for more stories like this. But I can't just say it's great for the story it was trying to tell, this movie in it's entirety just didn't work for me. Especially compared to all the other movies that came out this year. This isn't a Best Picture for me, this isn't a movie I will buy, cause I honestly don't see myself watching this again. Never know though, you might love it.
