As beautiful and heartfelt as a true-to-life story can get. Told with a brilliance of style and gut-punch honesty, this film doesn't miss a beat to surprise the audience. Those who are looking for more of a gay romance sort of film will be disappointed I think. This film is much more than that. It's about growing up and trying to find where you fit within the world around you but at the same time coming to terms with who you are as a person, for good or bad. It hits on so many levels that there should be something that each member of the audience can identify with. A stunning film and it's quite easily the best of the year.
